{
  "stem": "27748.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So she set up-- she converted an old barn into a mill, and made her own flour, and got into her Model T, and went around to stores, and sold her flour, simply out of conviction that that's what people should eat.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So she was that kind of a person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So in terms of my life, after I graduated from Guilford with high grades, I had applied to various universities for graduate school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "By then, I was convinced I wanted to be a sociologist, simply because I liked the subject matter, not because I really had any clear idea of what I wanted to do with it, or how I wanted to use it.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I was simply intrigued by it, and felt I could do something there in this field.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I was totally alienated and separate from anything Jewish, and certainly from the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wasn't thinking about the Holocaust at all, in terms of my life, or contributions anything like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I felt I wanted to go to a sociology graduate school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I applied to all the Ivy League schools.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some turned me down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But some, notably Harvard, accepted me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they didn't offer me any money, any fellowship money.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I saw no way of going there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But during-- after I was stuck in that situation, I was still living at Ada Field's house on her farm.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One of the people who came visiting her was the chairman of the sociology department at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, a man named Lee Brooks.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he heard my story, that I had applied and didn't have money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I hadn't applied at his university.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It so happened, the University of North Carolina was one of the leading schools in sociology in the country.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
